subject: RE: [Read_Alphabet] Re: Ikonboard Compromised By Spambots
msgSnippet: It s difficult to learn and stick with if you have no one to communicate with. I have been writing any notes in quickscript, and that helps. Why is it that
messageBody:
It's difficult to learn and stick with if you have no one to communicate
with. I have been writing any notes in quickscript, and that helps.

Why is it that most people seem to agree when you point out how silly the
written english language is, but think you are crazy for learning a more
sensible alternative?
I'm OK with the "crazy" label, but it seems funny to me.

Paul

>One method would be to learn only a few letters at a time. Pick out
>three consonants & two vowels (or whatever combination you'd prefer) &
>try to make as many words from that as you can.
>
>--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "Cheryl DEPPER" <depper_1@m...>
>wrote:
> > I've been having a tough time learning it. I don't seem to be able to
> > remember the script for each sound. I'll keep trying though.
> > Cheryl
